<h1>Soul Abrasion and Spell Casting Fury Update</h1>
	<B>The-Lionfist wrote: <BR><BR>Hi. <BR><BR>I can't help but noticing that the proposed fix for SCF and SA stacking doesn't make sense. <BR><BR>The way its described, you are actually being penalized for having SCF. <BR><BR>SCF succeeding would produce a lower crit value than SA would constantly since SA is not a "check" its a passive ability. <BR><BR>It makes more sense, to have SCF supressed for procs effected by SA -- not to actually have SCF have a chance to negate the perma-effect SA.</B> <BR><BR><BR>We've taken a second look at these abilities and the changes we proposed making yesterday. <BR><BR>We'll be finding a way to make them stack, so that should a critical happen the Life Tap will still check for and add the effects of Soul Abrasion. <BR><BR>Thank you for all of your input on the matter. <BR><BR>Alan


